	This is only a partial list of the ailments treated by 
Acupuncture and moxibustion; Oriental medicine could be applied to 
more ailments in combination with Western medicine for the welfare 
of all. More and more Medical Universities are combining both schools 
of medicine. Gynecologists are using Acupuncture to relieve labour 
pains and correct malposition of the fetus in the mother's womb. 
Dentists are using it as anesthesia for the extraction of teeth and 
operations on the gums.


				A FUTURE MEDICINE
	
	During the last few decades, scientific discoveries have caused 
an incredible expansion in the frontiers of knowledge. Revolutionary
breakthrough's, each with the potential equal to the discovery of 
gunpowder are now accelerating the pace of human affairs. Einstein's 
theory of relativity, high energy physics, decoding of the genetic 
space travel, the evolution of cybernetics and computers as a tool of 
human intelligence have been remarkable advancements. Despite the 
destructive applications of several discoveries, each possesses a 
common denominator. They all represent the expansion of human 
understanding into an area where logical reasoning seems no longer 
relevant or valid.

	Acupuncture and moxibustion, although effective is now on the 
threshold of being understood. As it's mechanisms are revealed through
